<p>In this post we'll see how the actual letters that make up crossword answers, in particular their vowels, channel the fill into certain predictable patterns.</p>

<h3>Vowel placement</h3>

<p>If you take a look at <a href="/short-answer-is#mostFrequentAnswers">the most common crossword answers</a>, it's obvious that vowels are pretty important. All of the most frequently-repeated answers are chock full of As. Es, Os, and Is. Here's a graph showing vowel usage:</p>

