<p>In the top left corner (row/column 1), a number of common words start with a consonant followed by a vowel: PAPA, HAHA, CASH, SPAM, BASH. In the second column and row, the most frequent words all start with vowels, and them have vowels in the third letter position. Because of the rarity of answers that start with vowels, these 2nd position 1st-row/column answers have much much higher frequencies, they're reused way more often, than the common answers in any other 1st-row/column position.</p>

<p>So what can you do about your headache? Well first of all, you can try to avoid using vowels in positions that will have to be the start of other answers. This is no easy task, but if you can concentrate your low-vowel words on the top row and left column, you'll be doing yourself a favor crosswordese-wise. Second of all, if possible, try to pick answers that stagger vowel usage so they don't fall into common patterns. Third of all, try anchoring somewhere other than 1-A and 1-D early on in the fill process and working from there, to break the pattern in the corners.</p>

